value.0: *a steely glint in his eye despite his advanced age* Well met ta ye. Have a look around, I've plenty for sale.
Eh?! This be O'Malley, ye daft ingrate! Damn fu'rgners, ye don't know nothin', do ya!
*disgruntled* ...aright then <lad/lass>, fire away if ye will

Hmm. Well if yer not interested in huntin' or the like, there be little work around here in O'Malley.

Come ta think of it though, I do have somethin' I be needin a wee bit o' assistance with. Ye willin' to journey to Corwell for me? Coin fer ye if ye do this.

Need ye ta get some goods from tha lad Uther there. Uther the Red. He calls hisself a tanner but, in truth, 'e's just a boy.

Uther used ta work for me 'ere, then took up with a lass in the city. But I still 'ave a fondness for the lad. Like ta purchase some o' his leathers now an agin, 'elp him along ye know. 

Fetch a parcel o' leathers from him an bring em to me here. I be needin' a restock o' the basic stuff anyhow.
The tannery in Corwell be yer destination then, <lad/lass>. Don't ye be strayin' from tha roads ye hear? Don't want ye ta end up as a bandit's bedroll, do we now?

Nay, there be plenty good huntin' around the Dafyd Heights to the south o' here, but that's the business of hunters, butchers and tanners. Ye'll find all three here in the village, or nearby at least. The hunters' camp and the tannery both be to the south o' the village, other side o' the Corwell road to us. The butcher be here in the village. They be the ones to talk to about huntin'.

Or ye can find tanners an' butchers over in Corwell of course... if'n ye don't mind city folk *sniffs*.

Ah, now there's a tale. Hunter most me life, see, 'till one day, tracking great beast in the forest over yonder, a <StartCheck>funny looking patch of dirt</Start> caught me eye. I sees it for what it is, site of <StartCheck>buried treasure!</Start>. I'm stuck into diggin' when the hairs stand up on me neck. Look up to see the very monster I'd been tracking. Only it's just, like, watching the dig. Hems me in when I try to leave. Starts to get toward night, and there's nowhere to go but down, so I take up the shovel and finish the job. There's the loot, gleamin' bright, but that's the last thing I'm worried about. Beast is already chargin' me, and it seems I'd never have stood a chance even if it were -I- who snuck up on -it-. Everything goes black...when I come to, it's near dawn, and I'm stiff and sore but still whole and the creature's gone! So had half the treasure, mind. The rest still netted me the seed money for this place, so all's well, eh?

Anywhere around the Dafyd Heights, tha' great ridge ye see o'er to the south, tha' be good huntin grounds. No bandits'll camp on the Heights either, they be a suspicious lot I do hear, think the woods there carry bad luck.

Ye may come across wolves an such e'en in parts of the Dafyd Heights. But if'n ye go direct south-east o' here, ye'll come to a right blessed part o' the slopes. Tis a beau-ti-ful place an' all. They say it be blessed by the Mother herself. 

No wolves or such will bother ye there, o' that ye can be sure.

*he pauses then shrugs, a distant look crossing his face* Must've been elvish work. Like wood, all branches and greenery, but of a fine stone by the way it caught the light. The light, aye, poured from it, between the twigs and leaves...*sighs deeply, sniffs* Never seen the like, or will again no doubt.

Well, now ye know what might be waitin' out there should ye go a-lookin'... plenty o' smugglers an pirates be buryin' their caches out in thae wilds. Tho' oft'n they be hidden fair well.

Jus' keep an eye out. Ye never know who might be watchin', ye ken?
It's ye, I remember ye. Did ye get tha' package from Uther, eh?
Well I'll be... ye came through. 'ere's yer payment, <lad/lass>.
Quick'n it up, ye hear? Uther be waitin' fer me ta collect the order, but I dinnae travel the roads no more.
*shrugs* ah wish ye had said so in tha first place then, ye ingrate. What do ye want then?
Where the heck am I? What is this place?
All right all right, I'm leaving *leave*
Fine, sorry. I'd like to ask you something else.
Changed my mind - I'm off
How did you get into the leather trade?
No thanks *leave*
I'm looking for work, don't suppose you are need of any assistance?
I'm no delivery <boy/girl> *leave*
Might be. What's the job?
No, I can't be bothered with this menial task. *leave*
I'm a delivery <boy/girl>, living in a delivery world. I accept your job.
I'll be careful.
You need leather for your goods right; will you pay me to hunt for you? Or for hides and meat?
All right, I'll go and ask at the tannery or the hunters' camp about hunting *leave*
Seems like hunting is what most people do around here. Were you ever a hunter yourself?
What have you for sale?
So I see. How did you get into the trade?
If you were a hunter, can you tell me where's the best place to hunt?
Thanks! Any other advice?
All right, thanks for the directions *leave*
You mentioned treasure...
Good to know. But you didn't tell me what an animal could have wanted with half that treasure you found!
Treasure? Sounds exciting. But what could an animal want with treasure?
*leave*
All very interesting. But where can I find some treasure of my own?!
A fascinating tale. Thank you.
Thanks for the advice, I really must be going!
Yes! Here it is *hand over the package*
Thanks! *leave*
Thanks! Now I want to buy things, or ask you questions or something
Not yet.
I'm no longer interested in doing your silly job for you. I just want to ask questions and buy things like a normal person. ((END the quest))
Actually nothing *leave*
You were a hunter once right?
All right *leave*
